quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  93,1,By the glorious morning light
  93,2,And the night when it is still
  93,3,"Your Lord has not forsaken you (Muhammad), nor is displeased with you"
  93,4,And surely the Hereafter is better for you than the present
  93,5,"And in the end your Lord will give you, and you shall be well pleased"
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan, and give you protection"
  93,7,"And find you wandering (or astray), and guide you"
  93,8,"And find you in need, and enriched you (or made you independent)"
  93,9,"Therefore, the orphan oppress him not"
  93,10,Nor the beggar (or petitioner) drive away
  93,11,"And as for the favour of your Lord, discourse (proclaim) thereof"